The Belgrade media have suggested that the success of the American restaurant depends on its acceptance by Yugoslavians who are long accustomed to the hamburger-like Pljeskavica. John Onoda, a spokesman at McDonald's Oak Brook, Ill. Pljeskavica is made of ground pork and onions, and it is served on bread and eaten with the hands. Negotiations have been going on for years for expanding the fast-food chain to the Soviet Union, but no agreement has been announced. , headquarters, said it was the first of the chain's outlets in a communist country. 